  76. ‌  let force_poly t =
  77.     match t.ptyp_desc with
  78.     | Ptyp_poly _ -> t

  81. ‌  let varify_constructors var_names t =
  82.     let check_variable vl loc v =
  83.       if List.mem v vl then
  84.         raise Syntaxerr.(Error(Variable_in_scope(loc,v))) in
  85. ‌    let var_names = List.map (fun v -> v.txt) var_names in
  86. ‌    let rec loop t =
  87.       let desc =
  88.         match t.ptyp_desc with
  89.         | Ptyp_any -> Ptyp_any
  90.         | Ptyp_var x ->
  91.             check_variable var_names t.ptyp_loc x;
  92.             Ptyp_var x
  93.         | Ptyp_arrow (label,core_type,core_type') ->
  94.             Ptyp_arrow(label, loop core_type, loop core_type')
  95.         | Ptyp_tuple lst -> Ptyp_tuple (List.map loop lst)
  96.         | Ptyp_constr( { txt = Longident.Lident s }, [])
  97.           when List.mem s var_names ->
  98.             Ptyp_var s
  99.         | Ptyp_constr(longident, lst) ->
  100.             Ptyp_constr(longident, List.map loop lst)
  101.         | Ptyp_object (lst, o) ->
  102.             Ptyp_object (List.map loop_object_field lst, o)
  103.         | Ptyp_class (longident, lst) ->
  104.             Ptyp_class (longident, List.map loop lst)
  105.         | Ptyp_alias(core_type, string) ->
  106.             check_variable var_names t.ptyp_loc string;
  107.             Ptyp_alias(loop core_type, string)
  108.         | Ptyp_variant(row_field_list, flag, lbl_lst_option) ->
  109.             Ptyp_variant(List.map loop_row_field row_field_list,
  110.                          flag, lbl_lst_option)
  111.         | Ptyp_poly(string_lst, core_type) ->
  112.           List.iter (fun v ->
  113.             check_variable var_names t.ptyp_loc v.txt) string_lst;
  114.             Ptyp_poly(string_lst, loop core_type)
  115.         | Ptyp_package(longident,lst) ->
  116.             Ptyp_package(longident,List.map (fun (n,typ) -> (n,loop typ) ) lst)
  117.         | Ptyp_extension (s, arg) ->
  118.             Ptyp_extension (s, arg)
  119.       in
  120.       {t with ptyp_desc = desc}
  121.     and loop_row_field field =
  122.       let prf_desc = match field.prf_desc with
  123.         | Rtag(label,flag,lst) ->
  124.             Rtag(label,flag,List.map loop lst)
  125.         | Rinherit t ->
  126.             Rinherit (loop t)
  127.       in
  128.       { field with prf_desc; }
  129.     and loop_object_field field =
  130.       let pof_desc = match field.pof_desc with
  131.         | Otag(label, t) ->
  132.             Otag(label, loop t)
  133.         | Oinherit t ->
  134.             Oinherit (loop t)
  135.       in
  136.       { field with pof_desc; }
  137.     in
  138.     loop t

  140. end
